The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Virendra Verma, 18 was arrested on Monday for allegedly stealing Rs 11 lakh from a locker of RK Shah Chartered Accountancy Firm in Ganesh Katra. Verma worked in the firm. He took the money after the office closed on Saturday and left for his ancestral home in Bihar, said cops. He returned on Monday morning, when the theft was detected. A team of officers have left with him for Bihar to recover the money.     Two persons were injured when a fire broke out in a chemical factory at Chanditala in Behala on Sunday night. The fire spread to a nearby factory. Police said the injured were admitted to Vidyasagar Hospital. Twelve fire engines brought the blaze under control after two and a half hours. Fire brigade sources said the blaze was probably caused by a short circuit. Search is on for the factory owner.    Water supply at Medical College and Hospital improved on Monday. The hospital has been facing water shortage for a week because of a malfunctioning pump. The supply at Eden ward was inadequate on Monday.     Bandana Dey, 26, hanged herself from the ceiling of her Nilmani Mullick Lane residence in Howrah on Monday morning. The body has been sent for post-mortem.     Residents of Metiabruz blocked Rameswarpur-Kachhi Sarak crossing for two hours on Monday morning demanding the arrest of those responsible for a clash on Sunday night. Two groups had fought over the possession of a plot. The men also threw bombs and bricks at police. Two persons were injured and three arrested.     Eleven people, including nine women, were arrested on Sunday night from Bishnupur for alleged involvement in flesh trade.     Eastern Railway will run a pair of special trains between Ranaghat and Shantipur on November 14, 15 and 16 for Ras Yatra. A pair of narrow-gauge special trains will also run between Shantipur and Nabadwip.                                                                                                                                                                 
